  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read root `MEMORY.md` to understand the existing feedback memory format (entries typically date-stamped, brief, action-oriented).</step>
    <step order="2">**Update (a)** root `MEMORY.md`: append a new feedback memory entry. Suggested form:
      ```
      ## 2026-06-05 — Communication architecture: do NOT add a 6th send-email implementation

      Per [ADR-033 Communication Architecture](.claude/adr/ADR-033-communication-architecture.md) and the [Communication Architecture Assessment 2026-06-05](docs/assessments/communication-architecture-assessment-2026-06-05.md), Spaarke has exactly ONE canonical client-side send-email path:

      - UI: `<EmailComposer />` engine via 3 wrappers (`<SendEmailStep />`, `<SendEmailDialog />`, `<SendEmailPage />`)
      - Programmatic: `sendCommunication()` typed wrapper in `@spaarke/ui-components/services/communicationApi.ts`

      **MUST NOT** add a 6th send-email implementation. If a new mount context emerges, add a 4th wrapper next to the existing three — do not bypass the engine. The R3 project (`email-communication-solution-r3`) closed the bug class created by 6 ad-hoc implementations. Re-fragmentation undoes that work.

      Triggers: any task with tags `communication`, `email`, `send-email`, or modifying `communicationApi.ts` / `EmailComposer*`.
      ```
      Adapt format to match existing MEMORY.md style.
    </step>
    <step order="3">**Verify (b)** root `CLAUDE.md` §16: confirm ADR-033 is reachable via the pointer table. Either:
      - A direct row referencing ADR-033 exists, OR
      - The "ADRs (concise)" row pointing to `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` covers ADR-033 (verify ADR-033 is in INDEX.md from Wave 0 task 001).
      If neither: add a direct row.
    </step>
    <step order="4">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 092 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `current-task.md`: status → completed, advance.</step>
  </steps>

